<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 2.3: PERFORMANCE DIAGNOSTICS - T 444E ENGINE -
        EXHAUST RESTRICTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="2">
        <title>EXHAUST RESTRICTION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Table
                    <hotlnk xrefid="t1901109">2.23</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                for the exhaust restriction test.
            </para>
            <table id="t1901109">
                <title>Table 2.23 Exhaust Restriction FROM FORM EGED - 195</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="144p"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="144p"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="144p"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="S1T3"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                                <para>Visually inspect exhaust system for damage</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                                <para>Check if EBP device is closing at high idle with breakout box pins 1+ and 19- on
                                    engine harness or "TEE" (green +) and (black -) (if so equipped)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                                <para>Measure at high idle</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>Instrument</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Specification</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Actual</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>DVOM</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>&#60; 2.0 Volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Purpose</title>
            <para>To determine if a restriction exists in the exhaust system which would cause an engine performance
                problem.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Visual Inspection</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect entire exhaust system for obvious physical damage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If exhaust system damage is not present, start engine and warm to operating
                    temperature.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Run engine at high idle with no load.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The exhaust back pressure valve should be open (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1901120">2.57</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                    illustrates positions of
                    <emph type="bold">tang</emph>
                    on bellcrank of the back pressure device when the exhaust back pressure (butterfly) valve is open
                    and closed. (If so equipped)
                </para>
                <figure id="f1901120" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg7344" filename="../figeg7/eg7344.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.57 Checking Position of Exhaust Back Pressure (Butterfly) Valve At High Idle
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Test Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the suspected exhaust restriction is not visually evident, an exhaust back pressure
                    measurement is necessary. Install the breakout box or "T"
                    <emph type="bold">(Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1901121">2.58</hotlnk>)
                    </emph>
                    in line with the EBP sensor which will allow access to the back pressure voltage signal.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Apply parking brake and insure the transmission is in neutral.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure exhaust back pressure (voltage) at high idle engine speed. Record voltage and
                    compare to voltage specification on diagnostic form.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Possible Causes</title>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Closed Exhaust Back Pressure device.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Collapsed tailpipe</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Clogged catalytic converter. (If so equipped)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Damaged muffler.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tools Required</title>
            <para>DVOM and sensor breakout "T" (ZTSE-4347), or breakout box (ZTSE-4445).</para>
            <figure id="f1901121" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg6334" filename="../figeg6/eg6334.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.58 Measuring Exhaust Back Pressure (Voltage)</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
